    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Peel and slice the<strong> red\u00a0onion<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong> into wedges</p> <p>Peel and finely dice (or grate!) the <strong>garlic</strong></p> <p>Peel and finely slice the <strong>ginger</strong> into\u00a0thin matchsticks\u00a0</p> <p>Dice the <strong>tomatoes</strong>, finely</p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/malabar-style-cauliflower-curry-and-basmati-rice/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Boil a kettle</p> <p>Chop the <strong>cauliflower</strong> into bite-sized florets, discarding the leaves</p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/malabar-style-cauliflower-curry-and-basmati-rice/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Heat a<span class=\"text-highlight\"> large, dry, wide-based pan</span> (preferably non-stick) with a matching lid over a medium heat</p> <p>Once hot, add the <strong>cashew nuts</strong> and cook for 2-3 min or until toasted, then remove from the pan</p> <p>Chop the <strong>toasted\u00a0cashew nuts</strong>,\u00a0roughly</p> <p>\u00a0</p> <p>\u00a0</p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/malabar-style-cauliflower-curry-and-basmati-rice/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Return the\u00a0pan to a medium-low heat with 2 tbsp <span class=\"text-danger\">[4 tbsp]</span><strong>\u00a0vegetable oil</strong>\u00a0</p> <p>Once hot, add the<strong>\u00a0red onion wedges</strong>, <span class=\"text-highlight\"><strong>ground</strong></span>\u00a0<strong>turmeric</strong>, <strong>ground coriander</strong> and <strong>ground fenugreek</strong></p> <p>Season generously with <strong>salt</strong> and cook for 5-6 min until the onions have softened</p> <p>\u00a0</p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/malabar-style-cauliflower-curry-and-basmati-rice/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, add the<strong> basmati rice</strong>, a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and 300ml <span class=\"text-danger\">[600ml]</span><strong> cold water\u00a0</strong>to a pot\u00a0with a lid and bring to the boil over a high heat</p> <p>Once boiling, reduce the heat to very low and cook, covered, for 10-12 min or until all the water has absorbed and the rice is cooked</p> <p>Once cooked, remove from the heat and keep covered until serving</p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/malabar-style-cauliflower-curry-and-basmati-rice/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once the onions have softened, add the <strong>garlic</strong> and\u00a0<span class=\"text-highlight\"><strong>half</strong></span> the <strong>ginger matchsticks</strong> and cook for\u00a02-3 min, stirring frequently, or until fragrant</p> <p>Once fragrant, stir in the <strong>tomato paste</strong> and add the <strong>cauliflower florets</strong> and give everything a good mix up</p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/malabar-style-cauliflower-curry-and-basmati-rice/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, remove the <strong>coconut cream</strong> from the sachet<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span> and chop it roughly\u00a0</p> <p>Dissolve 1/2 <span class=\"text-danger\">[1]</span> <strong>vegetable stock cube</strong>,<strong> tamarind paste</strong>,<strong> chopped coconut cream</strong> in 250ml <span class=\"text-danger\">[450ml]</span> <strong>boiled water</strong> \u2013 this is your<strong>\u00a0coconut\u00a0stock</strong></p> <p>Add the<strong> diced\u00a0tomatoes </strong>and<strong> coconut stock</strong> and cook, covered,\u00a0for 8-10 min or until the cauliflower is cooked through and the sauce has thickened to a curry-like consistency \u2013 this is your <strong>Malabar Cauliflower curry</strong></p> <p>\u00a0</p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/malabar-style-cauliflower-curry-and-basmati-rice/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>Malabar Cauliflower curry\u00a0</strong>over the<strong> rice </strong>and garnish with the\u00a0<span class=\"text-highlight\"><strong>remaining</strong></span><strong> ginger\u00a0matchsticks\u00a0</strong>and<strong> chopped cashews</strong></p> <p>Enjoy!</p>",
